Thousands of people are expected to attend the funeral service of former Hard Livings gang leader Rashied Staggie. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Thousands of people are expected to attend the funeral service of former Hard Livings gang leader Rashied Staggie. Staggie will be buried in Durbanville, Cape Town on Saturday. READ: Former Hard Livings boss Rashied Staggie shot dead The 56-year-old was gunned down while sitting in his car outside his home last Friday. Staggie's twin brother, Rashaad was shot and set alight by a vigilante group People Against Gansterism and Drugs in 1996.